meta.description: The manuscript is a collection of multiple English texts, mostly in verse. The language of J was localise in the Linguistic Atlas of Late Middle English in Soth-East Herefordshire (Laing, 1992: 571). As for textual relationships with other copies, stemmatologists proposed similatities between J and Ee. Moore () described J as a composite text which might have shared an exemplar with M as well as EeL (Hill, 1977: 100).
